\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {7.3}{\ignorespaces  The framework to revise model responses without introducing lesser-known facts. We iteratively (1) use \textsc  {FenCE}\xspace  to evaluate the factuality of each claim, (2) replace false information (if any) with the correct fact or remove it from the response, depending on whether it corresponds to a lesser-known fact, and (3) continue generating the next passage. For every claim, we prompt the generator ``\textit  {Is this claim factual?}'' without providing any source documents. If the generator outputs \textit  {``unknown''}, we assume that the claim corresponds to a lesser-known fact. \relax }}{74}{figure.caption.47}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:revise}{{7.3}{74}{The framework to revise model responses without introducing lesser-known facts. We iteratively (1) use \fencemodelname to evaluate the factuality of each claim, (2) replace false information (if any) with the correct fact or remove it from the response, depending on whether it corresponds to a lesser-known fact, and (3) continue generating the next passage. For every claim, we prompt the generator ``\textit {Is this claim factual?}'' without providing any source documents. If the generator outputs \textit {``unknown''}, we assume that the claim corresponds to a lesser-known fact. \relax }{figure.caption.47}{}}
\newlabel{fig:revise@cref}{{[figure][3][7]7.3}{[1][74][]74}}
